Paul C. Ney Jr. of Tennessee has been nominated to be the General Counsel of the Department of Defense. He has previously served as Chief Deputy Attorney General in the Tennessee Attorney General's Office and has been a partner in Patterson Intellectual Property Law, P.C. Ney has also held positions in the Department of the Navy, including Acting General Counsel and Principal Deputy General Counsel. He has received awards for his public service from the Department of Defense and the Department of the Navy. Ney holds a Juris Doctor and Masters in Business Administration from Vanderbilt University and a Bachelor's Degree in Biology from Cornell University. He has also served as a judicial clerk in the U.S. District Court for the Eastern District of Louisiana.